This is a tribute to the car that marked that era - YUGO and the youth that still modifies them today. ...more on www.bud3.net

The Zonta; a new Smart based car, made it’s world debut at the 2007 MPH shows. “Unfortunately I couldn’t make it, but I hear it did make quite an impression.”
It currently has 250BHP per tonne power to weight ratio with just a tiny tuned 700cc Smart engine! And whats best is the cost!

For around £13k you can get one of these custom built and painted for you!
Now compare this to the Ariel Atom which costs around £30k+.

This car looks like a beast from the front and look at those gorgeous 17″ wheels; I can`t wait to go and take it out for a test drive!

The only drawback and dislikes are the Smart seats (but I`m sure these can be pulled out and replaced) and unfortunately the rear of the car doesn’t have that smoothed off finish like the Atom, but if you could splice the back end style of the atom with the body of the Zonta this car to me would be perfect!

If I had a choice forget the cost between the Atom and Zonta, I would have to go with the Zonta its bigger, it looks more aggressive.

Fisker Automotive is an American automaker based in Anaheim, California [4]. The company's first product, the Fisker Karma is the world's first luxury plug-in hybrid electric vehicle (PHEV). It debuted at the 2008 North American International Auto Show, creating the premium green car segment in which most major manufacturers have since announced they would compete.

The Karma has a claimed total range of 300 miles (483 km), the first 50 miles (80 km) of which is on tailpipe-emission free electric-only charge. After 50 miles (80 km) a gasoline range-extending engine turns on to add an additional 250 miles (403 km) of range.

An estimated 15,000 cars per year will be assembled by Valmet Automotive in Uusikaupunki, Finland. Valmet currently builds the Porsche Cayman and Boxster sports cars for Porsche AG. The contract manufacturer was selected because a suitable North American facility could not be identified.

Fisker originally intended to start selling its Karma PHEV in late 2009, but, due to funding delays[citation needed], as of October 2010 it expects to begin customer deliveries in March 2011. The Karma S hardtop convertible concept unveiled at the 2009 North American International Auto Show in Detroit is planned to arrive in 2012, at an as-yet unstated price.

photo.title: Cobb Tuning R35 GT-R Time Attack Race Car

description._content: The Cobb Tuning race car. Stock motor, stock manifold modified slightly to bolt on Garrett GT2871 turbos, 3.5" 2-into-1 downpipes with a 3.5" exhaust. Essentially bolt-on turbos and the car puts out 788 awhp. Notice the 3.5" exhaust in the rear that turns the diffuser into a blown diffuser (creates a stronger low pressure zone in back and sucks the car down to the track). Aero package is widebody, custom sides and splitter, blown diffuser in rear and an Aeromotion adjustable wing. Hood is stock with a few vents. Brakes are nearly stock and it generates 1.7gs under braking! The wheels are Jongbloed 3305-Aeros.

View Large On Black This is my baby in her new home. It's been just over 5 years now when I brought her home shiny and new and completely stock from Acura but unfortunately I had to make the hard decision to let her go to make space for something different. People may find it silly to be attached to a car but this is more than a car to me. I got this car initially just to have a fun and stylish daily driver but because of it, I got deep into the autocross and track as well as the general car scene and made many of the friends I have today. It's evolved over the years to be a well balanced machine and as it grew, I grew. It got me 6 season championship trophies in Autocross, a 2nd in place trophy in the NorthEast divisional and a box full of other local event trophies. It got featured in Modified Magazine and me interested in photography. While some people would consider this a money dump, I considered it an investment in myself. The experiences and friendships I've had because of her over the past few years are priceless. So yes, it isn't just a car to me...it symbolizes a lot of personal growth and triumph over the past 5 years and I know it's gone to someone who can truly appreciate her in every way I did.

description._content: Snake River Car Show Labor Day Weekend in Huntington The annual Snake River Car Show in the historic town of Huntington Oregon. Great car show open to all categories including street rods, classics, customs, and modified cars of all models. This one day show on Main Street in front of the Lions Park in Downtown Huntington attracts cars from Oregon, Idaho and Washington and has quickly become an anchor Labor Day Weekend event for this small Eastern Oregon community located along the banks of the Snake River. For more information about the Snake River Car Show visit the Huntington Chamber of Commerce website at www.visithuntingtonor.org or for more information about other Baker County events and festivals visit the Baker County Tourism website www.basecampbaker.com/ or become a fan at www.facebook.com/basecampbaker
